# Concierge — scan preferences

_Last updated: (date) by (you or concierge)_

The concierge reads this before every user-directed scan (`--query "..."`).
**This is where you record how you like scans done** — summary style, what to
skip, when a discovery is also lead-worthy. The concierge folds feedback on its
finds into "Learned preferences" as dated bullets. Keep it under ~150 lines.

## Summary style

- (e.g. include phone number and street address in find summaries when known)
- (e.g. name the town in the summary — "in Rockland", "in Camden")

## What to skip

- Serving-area landing pages of out-of-region businesses ("<town> <service>"
  SEO pages with no local office) — not local businesses.
- Directory-listing-only entities (aggregator pages with no confirmable
  operating business behind them).
- (e.g. categories or entity types you never want in the feed)

## Lead guidance

- (When is a scan discovery ALSO a lead? e.g. "a good local business with a
  dated website or none — save as type 'lead' with a 0-1 fit score." See the
  prospector's profile for the full ICP; keep this section to the signals a
  scan can spot in passing.)

## Learned preferences

(The concierge appends dated bullets here, each citing the feedback that drove
it — e.g. "2026-07-10: user hid two mobile-service finds → prefer fixed-location
businesses unless the query says otherwise.")

## Standing instructions

- Answer the query first; enrichment (save_place / annotate_place) is the side
  mission, never a substitute for the report find.
- save_place only for businesses physically located in the region, with a real
  confirmed street address and the page you confirmed it at.
- Put exact facts in save_find/save_place; keep reasoning in notes/scans/.
